TITLE: Consumers' expectations of future inflation decreased significantly in win for the Federal Reserve
SUMMARY: The consumer outlook for inflation tumbled in July amid a sharp drop in gas prices and a belief that the surges in food and housing also would ebb.

TITLE: European stocks close higher as traders assess earnings, economic data
SUMMARY: European markets closed higher as investors continued to monitor corporate earnings and key economic data points, assessing recession risks.

TITLE: 'Echoes of the Cold War' as Blinken heads to Africa, vying with Russia for influence
SUMMARY: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken arrived in South Africa on Monday to begin a three-country tour, as major powers jostle for influence on the continent.

TITLE: Japanese giant SoftBank dumps its entire stake in Uber as losses mount at its investment unit
SUMMARY: SoftBank said it sold its remaining stake Uber as the Japanese conglomerate looks to raise cash amid mounting losses at its investment unit.

TITLE: Deadlock with Russia over Nord Stream gas turbine is not our fault, Siemens Energy CEO says
SUMMARY: The Kremlin has cut gas supplies to Europe via the Nord Stream 1 pipeline to just a fifth of its capacity.

TITLE: This 41-year-old left the U.S. for Bangkok and lives a 'luxurious lifestyle' on $8,000 a month
SUMMARY: Jesse Schoberg has been living abroad for 14 years, splitting his time between more than 40 countries — and he has no plans to return to the U.S. anytime soon.

TITLE: Palantir shares fall more than 12% following earnings report
SUMMARY: Palantir reported second-quarter results Monday that showed a loss per share compared with projections for earnings, but the company beat revenue expectations.

TITLE: Cash withdrawals in the UK soar as Brits grapple with the rising cost of living
SUMMARY: Brits are using cash as a way to manage their budgets as inflation in the country is expected to peak at over 13% in October.

TITLE: These are the top 10 best and worst places to live in the world—and you won't find the U.S. on either list
SUMMARY: The 2022 Economist Intelligence Unit’s Global Liveability Index ranked 172 cities across the world. These are the 10 best and 10 worst places to live.

TITLE: The price of a pint is going through the roof. Here’s why UK beer costs are far outpacing inflation
SUMMARY: The average cost of a pint of beer in the U.K. has soared by 70% since 2008 — well ahead of inflation.

TITLE: SoftBank posts a $21.6 billion quarterly loss on its Vision Fund, one of the highest in its history
SUMMARY: SoftBank posted a 2.93 trillion Japanese yen ($21.68 billion) loss for the June quarter for its Vision Fund. This is its second-largest quarterly loss.

TITLE: Video game giants had a miserable second quarter as the pandemic gaming boom hits a wall
SUMMARY: Microsoft, Sony and Nintendo each reported a fall in quarterly video game sales. The main reason? People are spending less time playing and more time going out.

TITLE: Hong Kong cuts hotel quarantine for travelers to 3 days, plus 4 days of home medical surveillance
SUMMARY: After completing the hotel quarantine, travelers can stay at home or in a hotel for the four days of surveillance.

TITLE: Baidu's robotaxis don't need any human staff in these parts of China
SUMMARY: Baidu announced Monday it became the first robotaxi operator in China to obtain permits for selling rides with no human staff inside the cars.

TITLE: Don't read vacation emails, keep your return date a secret and other tips for hacking your PTO
SUMMARY: Maximize your PTO like a VIP.

TITLE: Potential curb on Australian LNG exports is another blow to Asia-Pacific gas markets
SUMMARY: Energy protectionism is in full swing as Asia-Pacific LNG consumers prepare for a likely export cut from Australia, one of the top suppliers globally.

TITLE: 'I work just 5 hours a week': This 39-year-old makes $160,000 a month in passive income—a look at his typical day
SUMMARY: After Graham Cochrane lost his audio engineer job in 2009, he started a music blog. Now, what began as a side hustle has turned into a $160,000-per-year passive income stream. Working just five hours a week, here's what his typical day looks like.

TITLE: Bankrupt crypto lending platform Celsius withdraws motion to hire CFO back at $92,000 a month
SUMMARY: Celsius has withdrawn its motion to bring back ex-CFO Rod Bolger at $92,000 a month.

TITLE: Berkshire Hathaway reports operating earnings surge, but posts big investment loss amid market rout
SUMMARY: Berkshire Hathaway's operating profits jumped in the second quarter despite fears of slowing growth.

TITLE: Interviewing for your next job? Avoid this common mistake
SUMMARY: In a hot job market, the power seems to lie in the hands of job seekers. But that doesn't mean they'll make the best decisions when choosing their next jobs.

TITLE: Some consumers are cutting back on restaurant spending, but CEOs say not all chains are affected
SUMMARY: Bloomin' Brands, Restaurant Brands International and Starbucks said they aren't seeing changes in consumer spending.

TITLE: Fed Governor Bowman sees 'similarly sized' rate hikes ahead after three-quarter point moves
SUMMARY: Federal Reserve Governor Michelle Bowman said Saturday she supports the central bank's recent big rate increases and believes they should continue.

TITLE: Elon Musk challenges Twitter CEO Parag Agrawal to a debate on bots
SUMMARY: Elon Musk took shots at Twitter on Saturday, and dared CEO Parag Agrawal to debate him in the midst of a legal battle over a $44 billion acquisition gone awry.

TITLE: Netflix is expanding its push into video games, but few subscribers are playing along
SUMMARY: Netflix has been rolling out the games as a way to keep users engaged between show releases. But estimates suggest few subscribers are playing.

TITLE: Higher prices, skimpier portions and apps — how fast-food chains are changing value deals
SUMMARY: Fast-food chains have been working on providing focused value to consumers through mobile applications and rewards programs, as they pull away from traditional value menu offerings.

TITLE: Energy prices have dipped, but oil stocks are still a buy, investor says
SUMMARY: Oil prices have fallen sharply from their recent peaks, but there's still a case for buying oil stocks, according to Bill Smead of Smead Capital Management.

TITLE: Danger ahead: The U.S. economy has yet to face its biggest recession challenge
SUMMARY: You'd be hard-pressed now to find a recession in the rearview mirror. What's down the road, though, is another story.

TITLE: President Joe Biden tests negative for Covid-19 after rebound case
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden tested negative for Covid-19 but will continue to isolate, according to the White House.

TITLE: 'Stressed out' STD clinics struggle to handle surge in monkeypox patients as U.S. outbreak grows
SUMMARY: Sexual health clinics are facing a surge of patients seeking testing, vaccines and treatment for monkeypox.

TITLE: Bohemian noble family redefines modern aristocracy by selling NFTs to preserve and share a 700-year-old legacy
SUMMARY: A 27-year-old prince in Prague is trying to preserve and share his family’s 700-year legacy using NFTs, the blockchain, and the metaverse.
